FBIS4-19775 "drweu078_p_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 GREECE Bomb Blast Causes `Serious' Damage Bomb Blast Causes `Serious' Damage NC2204055594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 0400 GMT 22 Apr 94 NC2204055594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] The antiterrorism unit believes that the explosion of a powerful home-made time bomb that ignited at 2330 [2030 GMT] last night under a car was the work of 17 November and ELA [Revolutionary People's Struggle], or of ELA. The car, which was parked at the intersection of Rigas Fereos and Mesoyion Streets in the vicinity of the Pentagon [Greek National Defense General Staff headquarters], belongs to the Mille company. The explosion caused serious material damage to shops and buildings in the area.
